.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-2-3::.
The people use 7 different means of transport: snowmobile, motorbike, roller, train, quad-bike, skateboard, jet-ski
7 different games are played: go, backgammon, poker, snooker, mah-jongg, billiard, canasta
 1. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left of the person driving the snowmobile##1
 2. the person playing poker is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
 3. the person playing mah-jongg is the person driving the jet-ski##1
 4. the person driving the roller is on the left of the person driving the skateboard##1
 5. the person playing go is on the left of the person playing canasta##1
 6. the person driving the train is the person playing snooker##1
 7. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left of the person playing poker##1
 8. the person playing go is between the person playing canasta and the person driving the train##2
 9. the person driving the snowmobile is on the right of the person playing billiard##1
10. the person driving the motorbike is in the middle##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |    2    |    3     |    4    |   5    |   6    |     7     |
| Transport   | jet-ski | quad-bike | snowmobile | motorbike   | train | roller | skateboard |
| Game           | mah-jongg | billiard     | backgammon     | poker | snooker   | go   | canasta    |

